com.qualcomm.toq.smartwatch.api.v1.deckofcards.remote
Class DeckOfCardsManager

java.lang.Object
  com.qualcomm.toq.smartwatch.api.v1.deckofcards.remote.DeckOfCardsManager

public final class DeckOfCardsManager
extends Object

The manager class used by a client to interact with the remote Toq app's API service.

The manager will handle connecting to the Toq app's API service and provides a number of methods which a client can use to install, update and uninstall a deck of cards applet on the Toq smartwatch and send Toq notifications. The manager also enables a client to register listeners to receive connectivity and installation lifecycle events and to be notified with card events as the user interacts with cards in the deck of cards applet and notification pop-ups on the Toq smartwatch.

The methods in this class require the use of specialised remote implementations of the DeckOfCards, ToqNotification and ResourceStore classes which are specifically for use with the Toq app's API service.

Author:
mcaunter
See Also:
RemoteDeckOfCards, RemoteToqNotification, RemoteResourceStore

installDeckOfCards

public void installDeckOfCards(RemoteDeckOfCards deckOfCards)
                        throws RemoteDeckOfCardsException
Sends the deck of cards to the Toq app service, which in turn will install the deck of cards applet with a default launcher icon on the home screen of the Toq smartwatch. This method will trigger a Toq app UI interaction with the user, requiring the user to approve the installation before it can complete. Upon completion, the appropriate DeckOfCardsManagerListener.onInstallationSuccessful or DeckOfCardsManagerListener.onInstallationDenied listener method will be called.

Each client is only permitted to install a single deck of cards applet at a time. Attempting to recall install() if a deck of cards applet is already installed will return an error.

Parameters:
deckOfCards - the deck of cards
Throws:
RemoteDeckOfCardsException - thrown if the there was an error interacting with the service
Since:
1.4.0
See Also:
DeckOfCardsManagerListener

installDeckOfCards

public void installDeckOfCards(RemoteDeckOfCards deckOfCards,
                               RemoteResourceStore resourceStore)
                        throws RemoteDeckOfCardsException
Sends the deck of cards to the Toq app service, which in turn will install the deck of cards applet with the appropriate launcher icon on the home screen of the Toq smartwatch. This method will trigger a Toq app UI interaction with the user, requiring the user to approve the installation before it can complete. Upon completion, the appropriate DeckOfCardsManagerListener.onInstallationSuccessful or DeckOfCardsManagerListener.onInstallationDenied listener method will be called.

Customised deck of cards applet launcher icons can be added to the optional resource store and sent to the Toq app with the deck of cards. If no icons are specified, default launcher icons will be used.

Each client is only permitted to install a single deck of cards applet at a time. Attempting to recall install() if a deck of cards applet is already installed will return an error.

Parameters:
deckOfCards - the deck of cards
resourceStore - the resource store or null
Throws:
RemoteDeckOfCardsException - thrown if the there was an error interacting with the service
See Also:
DeckOfCardsManagerListener, DeckOfCardsLauncherIcon

sendNotification

public void sendNotification(RemoteToqNotification notification)
                      throws RemoteDeckOfCardsException
Sends the Toq notification to the Toq app, which in turn will forward the notification to the Toq smartwatch.

The Toq smartwatch will determine whether to update a currently visible pop-up or launch a new pop-up depending on the Toq smartwatch's current state.

A deck of cards applet must be installed before a notification can be sent.

Parameters:
notification - the notification
Throws:
RemoteDeckOfCardsException - thrown if the there was an error interacting with the service
